  "title": "Supply Chain Management (6 months contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Inventory &amp; Supply Planning</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor demand and plan supply needs accurately.</li>\n  <li>Lead regular meetings with the Project Manager to review inventory and forecasts.</li>\n  <li>Analyze data, prepare forecasts, and update them in the procurement system.</li>\n  <li>Set forecast limits and approve submissions.</li>\n  <li>Track slow-moving items and take action to meet inventory targets.</li>\n  <li>Plan ahead to keep stock levels at the right balance.</li>\n  <li>Monitor inventory across all product lines and track Days of Supply (DOS) and forecast accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate supply chain activities to support Singapore and regional teams.</li>\n  <li>Work with internal teams and external partners to align on demand, supply plans, production, and shipping status.</li>\n  <li>Process procurement data weekly and improve drop shipment processes.</li>\n  <li>Create purchase orders and manage product pricing in SAP, including updates and approvals.</li>\n  <li>Work with Product Managers and Japan HQ to solve pricing issues and release updated price files.</li>\n  <li>Manage weekly shipping schedules and dispatch plans.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Stock Allocation Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Distribute stock based on forecasts, requests, and excess inventory.</li>\n  <li>Carry out weekly stock allocation for shipments.</li>\n  <li>Reply quickly to stock requests and questions from sales companies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
